---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Healthcare | BeaconGuard for PHI-Sensitive Workflows"
  description="BeaconGuard enforces ALLOW or DENY decisions for PHI-sensitive healthcare workflows before governed execution, with Verifiable Decision Records for privacy and compliance review."
>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>Deterministic control for PHI-sensitive AI workflows</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard deploys alongside existing healthcare applications as a Runtime Control Boundary. It evaluates trusted request context against the Active Verified Release and returns ALLOW or DENY before governed execution, preserving Verifiable Decision Records for privacy, security, compliance, risk, and architecture teams.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Existing healthcare systems remain in place</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard does not replace the EHR, privacy office, clinical governance process, care-management platform, or other systems of record. Those systems remain authoritative. BeaconGuard enforces the request boundary before governed AI, APIs, or automated systems execute.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Scenario structure</h2>
    <p>
      Each scenario below follows the same review pattern: existing workflow, required trusted context, control evaluated, ALLOW or DENY result, why or when denied, evidence produced, and the system that remains authoritative.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Healthcare scenarios</h2>
    <div class="section-grid section-grid--scenarios">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Unapproved pathway for PHI-heavy summary</h3>
        <p><strong>Existing workflow:</strong> Operational summarization over PHI-bearing records.</p>
        <p><strong>Required trusted context:</strong> Approved pathway, role, source-system trust, freshness.</p>
        <p><strong>Control evaluated:</strong> Pathway approval against the Active Verified Release.</p>
        <p><strong>Result:</strong> DENY</p>
        <p><strong>Why / When denied:</strong> The pathway is not approved for this workflow.</p>
        <p><strong>Evidence:</strong> Verifiable Decision Record with release identity and decision context.</p>
        <p><strong>Authoritative system:</strong> EHR and clinical operations remain systems of record.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Required privacy approval absent</h3>
        <p><strong>Existing workflow:</strong> Privacy-gated operational AI assist.</p>
        <p><strong>Required trusted context:</strong> Privacy approval status and role boundaries.</p>
        <p><strong>Control evaluated:</strong> Approval requirement in the Compliance Playbook.</p>
        <p><strong>Result:</strong> DENY</p>
        <p><strong>Why / When denied:</strong> Required privacy approval is absent. An illustrative reason style is <code>APPROVAL_REQUIRED</code>.</p>
        <p><strong>Evidence:</strong> Verifiable Decision Record; governance review may follow without permitting execution.</p>
        <p><strong>Authoritative system:</strong> Privacy office and EHR remain authoritative.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Stale or replayed request</h3>
        <p><strong>Existing workflow:</strong> Patient outreach or operational follow-up assistance.</p>
        <p><strong>Required trusted context:</strong> Request identity, timestamps, freshness window.</p>
        <p><strong>Control evaluated:</strong> Trust, freshness, and replay checks.</p>
        <p><strong>Result:</strong> DENY</p>
        <p><strong>Why / When denied:</strong> The request is stale or appears replayed.</p>
        <p><strong>Evidence:</strong> Verifiable Decision Record capturing check outcomes.</p>
        <p><strong>Authoritative system:</strong> Care operations systems remain authoritative.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Approved operational request</h3>
        <p><strong>Existing workflow:</strong> Approved pathway with valid role and trust context.</p>
        <p><strong>Required trusted context:</strong> Signed/trusted metadata, pathway, freshness, role.</p>
        <p><strong>Control evaluated:</strong> Deterministic Playbook Evaluation against the Active Verified Release.</p>
        <p><strong>Result:</strong> ALLOW</p>
        <p><strong>Evidence:</strong> Verifiable Decision Record for later audit and reconstruction.</p>
        <p><strong>Authoritative system:</strong> EHR and workflow application remain systems of record.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>What BeaconGuard does not replace</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Electronic health records or clinical documentation systems</li>
      <li>Privacy office judgment or clinical governance</li>
      <li>Independent HIPAA certification or legal compliance attestation</li>
      <li>Probabilistic clinical diagnosis or model-hosted clinical reasoning</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="mailto:architecture@beaconguardassurance.com?subject=Healthcare%20Workflow%20Review">Request a Healthcare Workflow Review</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/docs/architecture">Review System Architecture</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
